grep, /bin/grep.sh
alias: 'grep'

Print lines of one or more files
that match a Lua pattern. To match
literal punctuation characters,
escape them with '%'.

Usage:
  grep [-i] [-n] [-v] <pattern> <file>...

  -i  case-insensitive match
  -n  prefix matched lines with
      the line number
  -v  invert match: print lines that
      do not match the pattern
